<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-09-09T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-09-09T22:00:00-05:00" n="515" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d515">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.003/411: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-09-10T11:00:00+08:00">September 10, 1930—11
                                    a.m.</date><lb/>[Received September 10—3
                            a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>796. Your 312, September 8, 6 p.m.,<note n="64" xml:id="d515fn64">Not
                                printed.</note> paragraph 3. Lampson showed me text of formula for
                            Hankow, Tientsin and Canton. I did not take a copy. My recollection is
                            that formula for Hankow and Canton was similar to that for Shanghai,
                            while Tientsin formula was altered to cover activity at Tangku.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>